
[1]mantle-tree

   MAN'TLE-TREE, n. The piece of timber or stone in front of a chimney,
   over the fire-place, resting on the jambs.

   [This word, according to Johnson,signifies the work over the
   fire-place, which we call a mantle-piece.]
